                            <comment id="12772204" author="chirag" created="Sat, 31 Oct 2009 01:27:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHINDIG-1215&quot; title=&quot;Honor the maxObjSize in BasicHttpFetcher and make it configurable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SHINDIG-1215&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SHINDIG-1215&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12772205" author="hsaputra" created="Sat, 31 Oct 2009 01:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe we could log something if the bytes read is greater than max object size.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12772619" author="plindner" created="Mon, 2 Nov 2009 19:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied with modifications.  I made these parameters optional and used setter injection instead.  Also made the max object size in bytes volatile and correctly closed the streams when we hit an error condition and return a 400 response instead of a truncated file.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
Paul&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
